"a.琐碎的；小心眼的 【英】 adj.琐碎的(trivial; unimportant);小心眼的( petty-minded) adj. 琐碎的; 微不足道的 = trivial 【记】pet宠物, ty小－小宠物－不重要的; ky结尾一般有小的意思 【参】kitty(n 小猫) 【类】petty: notice = mysterious: explain『contemptible: respect』小的不易被注意 = 神秘的不易被解释『可鄙的: 尊敬』 【记】pet宠物 + y 特点,宠物的特点就是小 petty (adj.)  late 14c., ""small,"" from phonemic spelling of Old French petit ""small"" (see petit). In English, not originally disparaging (as still in petty cash, 1834; petty officer, 1570s). Meaning ""of small importance"" is recorded from 1520s; that of ""small-minded"" is from 1580s. Related: Pettily; pettiness. An old name for ""Northern Lights"" was petty dancers."
